alternating$:$The flag "alternating" defines whether or not the animation should be alternate repeatedly. This happens only if the animation cycles more than once.
enabled$:$defines whether the animation may be executed

name$:$The name of the widget. The naming may be restricted by the project options.
Two widgets with the same direct parent may not have the same name

onPause$:$The reaction "onPause" is executed when the animation is paused.

animation_time
This is the time at which the animation is set to pause.

onPlay$:$The reaction "onPlay" is executed when the animation is started or continued.
The parameters are:
animation_time
This is the start time for the animation.

forward
This is the play direction. If it is true the animation goes forward and if it is false the animation goes backward.

onTerminate$:$The reaction "onTerminate" is executed when the animation terminates.
The parameters are:
animation_time
This is the length of time for which the animation was running.

terminate
This parameter specifies the reason for the termination:
0: normal termination due to animation completion

1: cancel triggered by the action f:animation_cancel

2: widget is destroyed due to view transition

3: jump to end, final step of animation is executed then the animation is canceled, caused by f:animation_cancel_end

4: reset and cancel, the first step of the animation is executed and then canceled, caused by f:animation_cancel_reset

repeat$:$Repeat is the number of cycles the animation runs.
If this property is set to zero the animation runs infinitely.
scale$:$The temporal "scale" multiplies the animation timing by the scale value.
alternating$:$define whether the curve should be repeated alternating
delay$:$delay in ms relative to the beginning of the animation
duration$:$duration of this curve segment in milliseconds
enabled$:$defines whether the animation may be executed

pl.a: Menu Button mit Icon und Text
Einfacher Icon-Button (z. B. als Basis fr Home-Button)
Status-Indikator bestehend aus zwei Bildern, die per "IndicatorIsOn" umgeschalten werden knnen. Wird z. B. fr die Blinker- und Lichtanzeigen verwendet.

Standard-View mit Hintergrund-Bild, Home-Button, Titel, sowie Statusanzeigen. Batterie-Status und Home-Button knnen bei Bedarf in einzelnen View-Instanzen unsichtbar geschalten werden (BatteryLevelVisible bzw. HomeButtonVisible). Das Hintergrundbild kann in den View-Instanzen gendert werden.
